President Obama called Iraqi Prime Minister-designate Haider al-Abadi to congratulate him on his appointment and express support for the formation of a new government in Iraq. They discussed the need for Iraqi leaders to address political issues and partner with the United States to strengthen the Iraqi Security Forces against ISIS. Both leaders agreed on the importance of forming an inclusive government representative of all communities. The President emphasized the readiness of the United States to deepen political and security cooperation with Iraq as political reforms are implemented. Prime Minister-designate Abadi thanked the President and expressed support for a strong partnership between the United States and Iraq.